However, this seems to change in all grids that have dimensions greater than 3x3 as seen above in the 4x4 grid. So far,
it seems to me that the only possible solution for a 4x4 grid would be the one above (excluding rotations and symmetry).

To prove that it would work for any grid larger than 4x4, let's look to a classic chess board with an 8x8 grid to solve 
the initial problem of the 8 queens who cannot attack each other we started in class.

