Likewise, it is most definitely possible to place 8 queens on a 8x8 grid so that they cannot attack each other. 

Although it takes a much longer time (possibly exponential given the different combinations of moves based on the size), 
an interesting experiment would be to test for which square grid sizes this does may work (apart from 2 and 3), if there are 
any to begin with. I had an interesting discussion with a few classmates at the Dojo yesterday and they seemed quite sure that
it would work for any larger number, which I agree with. Another possible experiment would be to test how fast a computer would be 
able to find the possible variations of different ways to place 8 queens on a 8x8 grid since a mere mortal like me took nearly 30 
whole minutes to figure just one out. 